SGX S&P CNX Nifty Index Futures Fall in Singapore Trading

-- B y   R e i n i e   B o o y s e n
-- 
2011-03-03T01:12:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/sgx-s-p-cnx-nifty-index-futures-fall-in-singapore-trading.html
The SGX S&P CNX Nifty Index futures
for March delivery fell 36 points, or 0.4 percent, to 5,483 as
of 9:06 a.m. in  Singapore  today.  The futures, derived from the 50 stocks on the underlying
S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock Exchange of  India  Ltd.,
fell 0.9 percent in Singapore yesterday and rose 3.9 percent to
5,543.85 in Mumbai at the close on March 1. Yesterday was a
holiday in India.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Linus Chua at 
 lchua@bloomberg.net  